    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><em>As you grasp a copper wire or other trinket, your lips move, but no sound comes out from your mouth. Instead, a creature nearby hears your words in their head. If they possess a matching trinket, they can respond in the same way.</em></p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>You say a message of up to 6 seconds in length silently (though your lips still move), and your target hears it in their head. If your target has a trinket that matches yours*, they can respond to your message in the same way.</p></li></ul></div></div><p></p><p><em>*This spell requires a conductive object as the material component. Most wizards are taught to cast this spell using a small piece of conductive wire, but any small metal object will do. Adventuring parties will often commission unique trinkets, such as iron pins, to form a message link.</em></p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><em>You can cast this spell through solid objects if you are familiar with the target and know they are beyond the barrier. Magical silence, 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood blocks the spell.</em></p></div>",
            "chat": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>You say a message of up to 6 seconds in length silently (though your lips still move), and your target hears it in their head. If your target has a trinket that matches yours*, they can respond to your message in the same way.</p></li></ul></div></div><p></p><p><em>*This spell requires a conductive object as the material component. Most wizards are taught to cast this spell using a small piece of conductive wire, but any small metal object will do. Adventuring parties will often commission unique trinkets, such as iron pins, to form a message link.</em></p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><em>You can cast this spell through solid objects if you are familiar with the target and know they are beyond the barrier. Magical silence, 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood blocks the spell.</em></p></div>"
